				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">How do you Raise CoV faction, bard style...<a name="9957"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 9 03 10:43 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hello all,
<br />
Quick background:
<br />
I killed in SS for several lvls when i was young (long long time ago) and got to Scowling (maybe even max)
<br />
I recently decided to repair my faction with Coldian and CoV.
<br />
SO, i spent 6 hours killing Giants in Kael solo (charm kiting mostly) and about an hour killing in a group.
<br />
Then i went on an AoW raid, but i came last so i missed all hits but 2 giants + AoW.
<br />
--Checked my faction with coldian: Threateningly!
<br />
--Checked my faction with CoV: Scowls :(
<br />

<br />
Next i spent 3 hours duoing with a lvl 50 pally in GD.
<br />
--Checked my faction with coldian: indifferent
<br />
--Checked my faction with CoV: Scowling :(
<br />

<br />
Now i heard this along time ago so i dunno how true it is
<br />
-2800 = Max Kos
<br />
-2800 to -801 = Scowling
<br />
-800 to -501 = Threatening
<br />
-500 to -101 = dubious
<br />
-100 to -1 = apprehensive
<br />
0 to 100 = indifferent
<br />
101-500 = Amiably
<br />
501-700 = Kindly
<br />
701-1199 = Warmly
<br />
1200+ = Ally
<br />

<br />
And that storm giants give +5 to CoV
<br />
and frost give +5 coldian and +1 CoV
<br />

<br />
So i dunno what the purpose is of all this data, but please tell me how you would recomend raising my CoV faction to ally.
<br />

<br />
Here i my Magelo so you can see what type of gear/aas and spells i have: http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=669067
<br />
</span></td>
