				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: How do you Raise CoV faction, bard style...<a name="9963"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 10 03 3:27 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Firstly try to get in on Vindi raids as much as possible, even if it's just for a tag.  Vindi has an emmense amount of faction increase for CoV.  Also see if any druids need help getting their gloves from Plane of Growth, once again the faction you get from killing those giants is quite nice.  Lastly, go on a mercenary slaughter campaign.  The mercenaries in EW and WL are really easy to kill and give +5 to CoV, as well you want to keep the merc broaches as once your faction is high enough you can turn them in 3 at a time for potions of draconic rage.</span></td>
